## What is Auto-configuration?

Spring Boot auto-configuration automatically configures Spring beans based on what's on the classpath, what beans are already defined, and what properties are set. It eliminates most boilerplate XML/Java config.

`@SpringBootApplication` is a composed annotation:
```java
@SpringBootApplication
// equivalent to:
@SpringBootConfiguration    // specialized @Configuration
@EnableAutoConfiguration    // triggers auto-config
@ComponentScan              // scans current package
```

## @Conditional Annotations

Every auto-configuration class uses `@Conditional` to only activate when appropriate:

| Annotation | Activates when... |
|---|---|
| `@ConditionalOnClass` | Class exists on classpath |
| `@ConditionalOnMissingClass` | Class is NOT on classpath |
| `@ConditionalOnBean` | Bean of type exists |
| `@ConditionalOnMissingBean` | Bean of type does NOT exist |
| `@ConditionalOnProperty` | Property has specific value |
| `@ConditionalOnWebApplication` | Running as a web app |
| `@ConditionalOnResource` | Resource file exists |

```java
@AutoConfiguration
@ConditionalOnClass(DataSource.class)          // only if JDBC on classpath
@ConditionalOnMissingBean(DataSource.class)    // only if you haven't defined one
@EnableConfigurationProperties(DataSourceProperties.class)
public class DataSourceAutoConfiguration {
    @Bean
    public DataSource dataSource(DataSourceProperties props) {
        return props.initializeDataSourceBuilder().build();
    }
}
```

## Auto-configuration Registration

In Spring Boot 2.x, auto-configs were registered in `META-INF/spring.factories`:
```
org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.EnableAutoConfiguration=\
  com.example.MyAutoConfiguration
```

In Spring Boot 3.x (Spring Framework 6), use:
```
META-INF/spring/org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.AutoConfiguration.imports
```
```
com.example.MyAutoConfiguration
com.example.AnotherAutoConfiguration
```

## Writing Your Own Auto-configuration

```java
@AutoConfiguration
@ConditionalOnClass(MyLibrary.class)
@ConditionalOnMissingBean(MyService.class)
@EnableConfigurationProperties(MyLibraryProperties.class)
public class MyLibraryAutoConfiguration {

    @Bean
    public MyService myService(MyLibraryProperties props) {
        return new MyService(props.getApiUrl(), props.getTimeout());
    }
}

@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "my.library")
public class MyLibraryProperties {
    private String apiUrl;
    private Duration timeout = Duration.ofSeconds(30);
    // getters/setters
}
```
